Joacim Cans (born 19 February 1970 in Mora, Sweden) is the lead singer of HammerFall, a Swedish heavy metal band. He is the only member aside from founder and guitarist Oscar Dronjak to appear on all of the band's albums.
Cans attended the Musicians Institute in Hollywood, California.
Cans participated with a choir team in the Swedish television program KÃ¶rslaget (the Swedish version of Clash of the Choirs) in 2008.
On 10 May his team won the competition.
